<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL RIDE OPTIMIZED SUSPENSION (IROS) - Checking U-Bolt Nut Torque and U-Bolt Nut Tightening
        Procedure
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Checking U-Bolt Nut Torque and U-Bolt Nut Tightening Procedure</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect the U-bolt threads and U-bolt nuts for rust and debris and clean threads if
                contaminated.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using a torque wrench determine the torque required to turn the U-bolt nuts while tightening
                (clockwise rotation)
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using the lowest nut torque discovered as the reference starting point, re-tighten the nuts
                using the sequence noted in "Installing U-bolts and U-Bolt nuts".
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
